Put it together

We can put all of these data transformation actions together using the |&gt; function

line 1: creates new dataframe called bracero_clean
line 2: creates formatted date column called date_format from the original date column.
line 3: selects for all columns except for the old date column
line 4: renames the title column to interviewee
line 5: moves the indentifier column to after the date_format column.



bracero_clean &lt;- bracero |&gt;
  mutate(date_format = as.Date(date)) |&gt; 
  select(-date) |&gt; 
  rename("interviewee" = "title") |&gt; 
  relocate(identifier, .after = date_format)

ggplot

ggplot functions just like pipes (i.e., each line should end with a +)


county_vars_1930 |&gt;
  group_by(state) |&gt;
  summarize(
    sum_total_pop = sum(total_pop)
  ) |&gt;
  ggplot(aes(state, sum_total_pop)) +
  geom_col() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))

